<body>
    <h1>Q-77. What are all the looping structures in JavaScript?</h1>
   
    <h2>Ans :</h2>
    <p> looping structure are allow repeatedly Execute The code if condition is true</p>
   <h2> - Looping structures in JavaScript</h2>
    <p>1. for loop</p>
    <p>2. while loop</p>
    <p>3. do while loop</p>
    <p>4. for of loop</p>
    <p>5. for in loop</p>

    <h2>Example :</h2>
    <div>&lt;script&gt;</div>
    <div><pre>

        1. for loop:

        for (initialization; condition; update) {
            // code to be executed
          }
      ---------------------------------------------------
      
      2. while loop:

      while (condition) {
        // code to be executed
      }
     
      ---------------------------------------------------

      3. do while loop:
      
      do {
        // code to be executed
      } while (condition);
      
    
     ----------------------------------------------------

     4. for of loop:

     for (variable of iterable) {
        // code to be executed
      }

     -----------------------------------------------------

    5. for in loop:

    for (variable in object) {
        // code to be executed
      }
</body>

